 centre. Despite yellow weather warnings and significant disruption to train travel, revellers were undaunted. The festival was set to attract up to 30,500 people, including community groups, small businesses and NHS.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 16:16:29 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/05/wind-and-rain-fails-to-dampen-spirits-at-brighton-pride-festival" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/aug/05/uk-experts-fear-losing-access-to-ice-age-mammoths-cotswolds-site-to-uae" target="_blank">UK experts fear losing access to ice age mammoths Cotswolds site to UAE - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Archaeologists and palaeontologists say legislation needed to protect major finds championed by David Attenborough. They are calling for changes to the law amid fears that evidence at a site in the Cotswolds could be lost to the UK for ever. Fears that crucial evidence at the site, which is under threat, could also be lost forever.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 14:18:55 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/aug/05/uk-experts-fear-losing-access-to-ice-age-mammoths-cotswolds-site-to-uae" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/05/the-kinks-former-keyboardist-john-gosling-dies-aged-75" target="_blank">The Kinks’ former keyboardist John Gosling dies aged 75 - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Members pay tribute to ‘great man’ who played with band in 1970s. Gosling joined the Kinks in 1970 as a keyboard player. Brothers Ray and Dave Davies formed the band in the 1960s, with Gosling joining in 1970. The Kinks have paid tribute to their former bandmate John Gosling.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 15:34:35 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/05/the-kinks-former-keyboardist-john-gosling-dies-aged-75" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/05/simon-squibb-stairwell-small-businesses-entrepreneurs-twickenham-london" target="_blank">‘One step at a time’: entrepreneur buys stairwell in London to help startups - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Simon Squibb spent £25,000 on a disused stairwell in Twickenham, south-west London. He plans to provide rent-free space for small businesses to fulfil their dreams. The entrepreneur retired at 40 after selling Fluid, his marketing agency, to PricewaterhouseCoopers.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 12:31:56 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/05/simon-squibb-stairwell-small-businesses-entrepreneurs-twickenham-london" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2023/aug/05/russia-ukraine-war-live-russian-tanker-hit-by-drones-saudi-arabia-talks-will-be-difficult-says-kyiv-envoy" target="_blank">Russia-Ukraine war live: Moscow promises retaliation over tanker attack - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Ukrainian drone said to have struck ship in Kerch Strait just one day after Russian Black Sea fleet vessel hit. Anonymous security service source said: 'Overnight the [Ukrainian security service] SBU blew up the Sig, a large oil tanker of the Russian Federation that was transporting fuel for Russian troops'</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 16:52:57 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2023/aug/05/russia-ukraine-war-live-russian-tanker-hit-by-drones-saudi-arabia-talks-will-be-difficult-says-kyiv-envoy" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/05/oligarchs-fret-about-their-assets-as-uk-fights-to-keep-tabs-on-their-spending" target="_blank">Oligarchs fret about their assets as UK fights to keep tabs on their spending - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Le Grand Bleu is one of the largest superyachts ever to sail the seven seas. The 113-metre-long vessel belongs to Eugene Shvidler, a Russian-born oil tycoon who was sanctioned by the UK last year. The Treasury faces a mountain of paperwork and criticism that it is being too lenient.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 15:00:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/05/oligarchs-fret-about-their-assets-as-uk-fights-to-keep-tabs-on-their-spending" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/04/russian-soprano-anna-netrebko-met-opera-russia" target="_blank">Top Russian soprano axed over Ukraine invasion sues Met Opera - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Anna Netrebko asks for at least $360,000 in damages for lost performance and rehearsal fees. She claims the Met caused ‘severe mental anguish and emotional distress’ that included “depression, humiliation, embarrassment, stress and anxiety, and emotional pain and suffering”</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 18:35:21 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/04/russian-soprano-anna-netrebko-met-opera-russia" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/05/heaven-review-traverse-edinburgh-eugene-obrien" target="_blank">Heaven review – the bittersweet taste of love - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Eugene O'Brien’s Heaven is set on the weekend of a spirited wedding in Edenderry in the Irish midlands. A fiftysomething couple find themselves reckoning with a romanticised past and an uninspiring present. A compellingly acted, exquisitely written play by Eugene O’Brien.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 16:02:57 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/05/heaven-review-traverse-edinburgh-eugene-obrien" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/05/my-boat-was-attacked-by-orcas-too-what-does-this-say-about-the-sea" target="_blank">Orcas ‘attacked’ my boat too. What does this say about the sea? - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Violent interactions with humans off the Iberian coast have caused alarm but mystery still surrounds the apex predators. Two pods of orca preying on sperm whale calves were defeated by adult whales who had gathered around to defend their young. The orcas then turned their attention to our 6m fishing boat, circling us, before ramming our prow. Five of the orcas swam directly at our side, creating a compression wave as if to tip us over.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 13:33:55 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/05/my-boat-was-attacked-by-orcas-too-what-does-this-say-about-the-sea" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/aug/05/derek-guy-the-notorious-fashion-tweeter-on-sunaks-short-trousers" target="_blank">Derek Guy: the notorious fashion tweeter on Sunak’s short trousers - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> US menswear critic Derek Guy keeps a close eye on politicians and says ‘they all dress equally badly’ Images of Rishi Sunak's shrunken trousers flooded social media long before he boarded the plane. ‘I don’t think he has a grand theory for how short sleeves and pants make him look taller’</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 08:00:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/aug/05/derek-guy-the-notorious-fashion-tweeter-on-sunaks-short-trousers" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/05/this-is-how-we-do-it-were-expecting-another-baby-and-its-turbocharged-our-sex-life" target="_blank">This is how we do it: ‘We’re expecting another baby, and it’s turbocharged our sex life’ - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Olivia and Finlay had sex off the menu for a time after their first child. But their second pregnancy is making them horny – and creative – again. Olivia says: 'My libido is surging and I suddenly want it all the time, which is thrilling' As a parent, sex becomes like sleep: you get it when you can, Olivia says.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 11:00:41 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/05/this-is-how-we-do-it-were-expecting-another-baby-and-its-turbocharged-our-sex-life" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/05/comedians-worst-edinburgh-ed-byrne-grace-campbell-john-robins-olga-koch-paul-sinha" target="_blank">‘I almost died. Just kidding! I only broke my leg’: comedians share their Edinburgh fringe horror stories - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The fringe can take its toll, but it’s all good material, right? Ed Byrne, Paul Sinha, Olga Koch et al have lived to tell the tale. One night I had my first encounter with Buckfast and got to sleep at 7am. Another day I had to be up at 10am to flyer our show.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 10:55:39 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/05/comedians-worst-edinburgh-ed-byrne-grace-campbell-john-robins-olga-koch-paul-sinha" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/05/its-more-february-than-august-holidaymakers-sit-out-storm-in-cornwall" target="_blank">‘It’s more February than August’: holidaymakers sit out storm in Cornwall - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Britain’s soggy summer is enough to make you give up and head to the Med. Yet families are happily splashing around on the beach in St Ives, Cornwall. Kate and Tilly Perrett look as if they might be regretting taking their summer holiday in Cornwall.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 15:10:29 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/05/its-more-february-than-august-holidaymakers-sit-out-storm-in-cornwall" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/05/a-bonkers-gig-how-heavy-metal-bands-are-helping-keep-uk-church-organs-alive" target="_blank">‘A bonkers gig’: how heavy metal bands are helping keep UK church organs alive - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Heavy metal bands Arð and Pantheïst performed at Huddersfield town hall accompanied by the organ. The Organic Doom gig was so successful that they plan to repeat the performance around the UK. The hope is that events like these will help save some of the nation’s pipe organs from destruction.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 15:11:13 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/05/a-bonkers-gig-how-heavy-metal-bands-are-helping-keep-uk-church-organs-alive" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/05/meg-2-the-trench-review-another-fin-mess-for-jason-statham" target="_blank">Meg 2: The Trench review – another fin mess for Jason Statham - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Ben Wheatley’s prehistoric shark sequel comes adrift in a surfeit of new lizardy threats, a clunking screenplay and a total lack of onscreen chemistry. The Meg 2 brazenly steals from other pictures and throws a bunch of extra creatures into the mix. Not only are multiple megalodons; there is a pack of ocean-dwelling fish-lizard-creatures so savage that they seem to have an extra set of teeth on their chins.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 13:00:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/05/meg-2-the-trench-review-another-fin-mess-for-jason-statham" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/05/england-womens-world-cup-katie-zelem-nigeria" target="_blank">Katie Zelem ready to run England midfield after seizing second chance - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Katie Zelem was left out of last England camp before Sarina Wiegman named her World Cup squad. Manchester United midfielder has picked up her first start for the Lionesses at the World Cup. She will probably play an important role in England’s last-16 tie with Nigeria on Monday.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 13:43:12 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/05/england-womens-world-cup-katie-zelem-nigeria" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/05/japan-norway-womens-world-cup-last-16-report" target="_blank">Japan advance to World Cup last eight as Hinata Miyazawa strike sinks Norway - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Japan beat Norway 3-1 to reach the quarter-finals of the Women’s World Cup in Wellington. Risa Shimizu and Hinata Miyazawa scored second-half goals for the Japanese. Guro Reiten had levelled for Norway in the first half, heading home after an own goal from Ingrid Engen.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 10:21:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/05/japan-norway-womens-world-cup-last-16-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/05/uswnt-sweden-world-cup-knockout-stage-preview" target="_blank">Struggling USA out for World Cup reset against familiar foes Sweden - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Sweden and the United States have met in six of the past eight World Cups, but never in the knockout rounds. The U.S. women hope to avoid the worst finish in program history. The United States women also don't look anything like a team playing well enough to win a World Cup.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 13:39:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/05/uswnt-sweden-world-cup-knockout-stage-preview" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/05/switzerland-spain-womens-world-cup-last-16-report" target="_blank">Spain surge into World Cup quarters as Bonmatí leads rout of Switzerland - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Aitana Bonmatí scored a brilliant double and was at the heart of everything good for the European powerhouses. Laia Codina scored at both ends with Alba Redondo and Jennifer Hermoso also on target at Eden Park. Spain into the Women’s World Cup quarter-finals for the first time.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 07:25:11 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/05/switzerland-spain-womens-world-cup-last-16-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2023/aug/05/wales-v-england-rugby-world-cup-warm-up-international-live" target="_blank">Wales v England: Rugby World Cup warm-up international – live - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Wales kick off at 5.30pm BST kick-off in Cardiff. Ryan Elias is off with an injury, replaced with Elliot Dee. Scotland kick off against Wales in the Welsh capital at 5pm BST. Scotland travel to Cardiff to face Wales in their first Autumn International Test on Saturday.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 16:59:31 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2023/aug/05/wales-v-england-rugby-world-cup-warm-up-international-live" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/05/boxing-dillian-whyte-returns-adverse-test-anthony-joshua-rematch-off" target="_blank">Dillian Whyte vows to prove innocence over ‘adverse’ test with Joshua fight off - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Dillian Whyte returned ‘adverse analytical findings’ in anti-doping test. Boxer insists he is ‘completely innocent’ as rematch with Anthony Joshua is called off. Matchroom cancels fight with Joshua after Voluntary Anti-Doping Association informed promoters and boxing authorities.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 12:27:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/05/boxing-dillian-whyte-returns-adverse-test-anthony-joshua-rematch-off" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/05/england-new-zealand-netball-world-cup-semi-final-report" target="_blank">England outlast New Zealand to reach Netball World Cup final for first time - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> England reach Netball World Cup final for first time after beating New Zealand 46-40 in semi-final. Roses will face Australia in their first final at the tournament in Cape Town. Jess Thirlby’s team went toe-to-toe with the Silver Ferns in an unrelenting contest.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 10:58:42 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/05/england-new-zealand-netball-world-cup-semi-final-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/05/watford-qpr-championship-report" target="_blank">Watford blow away abject QPR with four-goal demolition job in first half - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The opening weekend of the season is meant to be a time of universal optimism, when fans can bask in the sunshine and dream about a campaign which is yet to take shape. Watford and QPR arrived at Vicarage Road in a fog of unknowns with fans h