trong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/05/four-teens-arrested-over-death-of-18-year-old-in-bournemouth" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/05/at-home-with-tyson-fury" target="_blank">At home with Tyson Fury: ‘I do the bins, I do the school run and I love picking up the dog poo’ - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> At Home With the Furys is a nine-part fly-on-the-wall reality series due to hit Netflix later this month. The heavyweight champion talks marriage, mental health and why he’s invited the cameras in to make the show. Fury: 'I’m sorry about all this,” Paris will occasionally say, but the truth is that she's got the chaos under control.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 06:00:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/05/at-home-with-tyson-fury" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/05/i-cried-with-anger-the-trials-and-torment-when-travelling-with-blindness" target="_blank">‘I cried with anger’: the trials and torment when travelling with blindness - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> A train guard accused me of faking blindness when I was travelling from Cambridge to London. Society needs to be educated about the nuances of sight loss. There were extensive apologies, and I went home and cried. With anger. The train guard apologised for his actions, but I lost my temper and put out my false eye.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 13:00:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/05/i-cried-with-anger-the-trials-and-torment-when-travelling-with-blindness" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/05/one-of-last-photos-of-queen-elizabeth-ii-up-for-national-award" target="_blank">One of last photos of Queen Elizabeth II up for national award - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> People invited to choose from 20 images taken in 2022 for the UK Picture Editors’ Guild Awards. People can choose from photos taken between 1 January and 31 December 2022 for photo of the year at the annual awards. One of the last public pictures of the late Queen Elizabeth II is up for an award.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 06:00:35 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/05/one-of-last-photos-of-queen-elizabeth-ii-up-for-national-award" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/05/wildlife-lovers-fear-for-nature-reserve-threatened-by-cambridge-university-building" target="_blank">Wildlife lovers fear for nature reserve threatened by Cambridge university building - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Paradise nature reserve on the banks of the river Cam is home to eight species of bat, including the rare and endangered barbastelle. The tiny 2.2 hectare reserve protects the river corridor between Cambridge city centre and Grantchester Meadows. It has been popular with Cambridge students, college dons and nature-lovers for centuries.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat,