aring evidence with unauthorized people after post on Truth Social. Trump spokesperson said post was the ‘definition of political speech’ protected by the constitution’s first amendment and that it did not have to do with the criminal case.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 16:35:20 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/05/donald-trump-threatening-social-media-post-flagged-by-prosecutors-in-court-filing" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/05/travis-king-us-declines-prisoner-of-war-norht-korea" target="_blank">US declines to classify soldier who entered North Korea as prisoner of war - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Travis King is detained in North Korea after crossing into the country last month. Decision could mean he is not covered by the protections entitled to prisoners of war under Geneva conventions. Decision is highly sensitive for US military given commitment to leave no soldier behind enemy lines. King could not be classified as a prisoner of war because he crossed into North Korea.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 13:34:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/05/travis-king-us-declines-prisoner-of-war-norht-korea" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/05/texas-judge-rules-abortion-ban-too-strict-for-risky-pregnancies" target="_blank">Texas judge rules abortion ban too strict for risky pregnancies - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Ruling in Austin was the first to undercut the law since it took effect in 2022. State attorney general immediately appeals against ruling that says doctors must be allowed to end unsafe pregnancies. Ruling delivers a major victory to abortion rights supporters, who see the case as a potential blueprint to weaken restrictions elsewhere.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 08:49:12 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/05/texas-judge-rules-abortion-ban-too-strict-for-risky-pregnancies" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/04/lucky-border-terrier-makes-incredible-journey-100-miles-across-switzerland" target="_blank">Border terrier makes incredible journey 100 miles across Switzerland - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Lucky was left in kennels in Bern but escaped and made her way to Lake Geneva. The 14-year-old border terrier made an epic 100-mile journey across Switzerland on the eve of the country’s national holiday. Lucky was found and traced to owners and returned to her owners.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 18:53:57 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/04/lucky-border-terrier-makes-incredible-journey-100-miles-across-switzerland" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/04/kai-cenat-influencer-twitch-youtube-arrested" target="_blank">NYPD officers detain online influencer after giveaway devolves into chaos - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Kai Cenat, 21, a streamer, had announced the event to his several million followers and crowds surged beyond control. Police were mulling possible criminal charges such as inciting a riot, NYPD chief of department said in the evening. Police are considering possible charges of inciting riot, Jeffrey Maddrey said.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 00:51:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/04/kai-cenat-influencer-twitch-youtube-arrested" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/04/mark-margolis-dead-breaking-bad-better-caul-saul" target="_blank">Breaking Bad actor Mark Margolis dies aged 83 - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Margolis played drug lord Hector Salamanca in Breaking Bad and Better Call Saul. He also appeared in Scarface and The Wrestler. Margolis died at Mount Sinai Hospital in New York City following a short illness. His wife, Jacqueline, and son, Morgan, were at his bedside.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 17:07:01 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/04/mark-margolis-dead-breaking-bad-better-caul-saul" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/05/kenya-police-haiti-human-rights-concerns" target="_blank">Kenya’s offer to send police to Haiti sparks human rights concerns - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Human rights groups say move could worsen country’s security crisis given police force's poor human rights record. Move welcomed by officials in the embattled Caribbean nation, but prompted concern among human rights groups who say it could worsen the country's security crisis. Prime minister Ariel Henry requested international support from the UN last year when gangs began taking control of much of the country.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 11:15:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/05/kenya-police-haiti-human-rights-concerns" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2023/aug/05/a-year-on-the-devastating-long-term-effects-of-pakistans-floods-are-revealed" target="_blank">A year on, the devastating long-term effects of Pakistan’s floods are revealed - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Islamic Relief says rich nations must compensate those suffering worst of climate crisis. 40% of children in flood-affected areas had stunted growth and 25% were underweight. 80% of mothers reported sickness among children, with outbreaks of diarrhoea, malaria and dengue fever increasing.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 06:00:36 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2023/aug/05/a-year-on-the-devastating-long-term-effects-of-pakistans-floods-are-revealed" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/05/can-i-bring-my-switch-a-family-holiday-throws-up-existential-questions" target="_blank">‘Can I bring my switch?’: A family holiday throws up existential questions - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Paul Murray spent four months teaching in Boston with his wife and son. He wanted to give his 10-year-old son a trip of a lifetime to New York. The writer wanted to take full advantage of his holiday pay and immerse himself in another culture. New York City is the opposite of a bleak field in Cork.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 08:00:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/05/can-i-bring-my-switch-a-family-holiday-throws-up-existential-questions" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/05/good-morning-scotland-rishi-sunak-martin-geissler-review-ralph-mclean-show-sinead-oconnor-tribute-drowned-the-flooding-of-a-village-capel-celyn-on-the-wire-steve-barker-back-to-now-podcast" target="_blank">The week in audio: Good Morning Scotland; The Ralph McLean Show; Drowned: The Flooding of a Village and more – review - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> It’s been a good week for local radio, from Martin Geissler skewering of the PM on BBC Radio Scotland to a Sinéad O’Connor tribute to beat them all. Rishi Sunak's turn on Good Morning Scotland was a delightfully spleen-twisting slice of schadenfreude. The clip of him defending his private jet journeys went viral.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 16:00:46 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/05/good-morning-scotland-rishi-sunak-martin-geissler-review-ralph-mclean-show-sinead-oconnor-tribute-drowned-the-flooding-of-a-village-capel-celyn-on-the-wire-steve-barker-back-to-now-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/04/i-love-you-i-hate-you-the-on-screen-couples-whose-tv-roles-tore-them-apart" target="_blank">‘I love you, I hate you’: the on-screen couples whose TV roles tore them apart - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Jessica Chastain has claimed that working with Oscar Isaac ruined their friendship. The pair have been feuding off set for HBO's Scenes from a Marriage. The actress says she doesn't seem to like Isaac any more because of it. She said: 'Our friendship has never quite been the same'</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 15:00:16 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/04/i-love-you-i-hate-you-the-on-screen-couples-whose-tv-roles-tore-them-apart" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/05/johnathan-blake-passage-review-pentad" target="_blank">Johnathan Blake: Passage review – a vibrant tribute to his father - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The Philadelphia drummer reunites his much-praised quintet for an uplifting tribute, featuring lush vibes, funky jams and irrepressible energy. A tribute to his late father, violinist John Blake Jr, it’s a vibrant, varied set in which all five players get to shine.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 15:00:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/05/johnathan-blake-passage-review-pentad" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/05/this-much-i-know-pam-ayres-i-inherited-a-love-of-english-from-my-mother" target="_blank">Pam Ayres: ‘I inherited a love of English from my mother’ - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The poet, 76, talks about deference, dialect and dreams of becoming a ballerina. She grew up in a very feudal village where forelock tugging went on. Her father apologised for speaking in dialect, as if it was something to be ashamed of.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 13:00:42 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/05/this-much-i-know-pam-ayres-i-inherited-a-love-of-english-from-my-mother" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/aug/05/on-my-radar-alabaster-deplume-cultural-highlights" target="_blank">On my radar: Alabaster DePlume’s cultural highlights - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Alabaster DePlume is a spoken word poet and saxophonist based in London and Manchester. His new album, Come With Fierce Grace, is released on International Anthem on 8 September. In 2020 he released To Cy & Lee: Instrumentals Vol. 1, named after two men he assisted as a mental health support worker.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 14:00:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/aug/05/on-my-radar-alabaster-deplume-cultural-highlights" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jun/27/next-stop-spain-how-to-start-your-european-road-trip-on-the-sea" target="_blank">Next stop Spain: how to start your European road trip on the sea - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Katie Nicholson and Ciaran Nicholson have fallen in love with the comfort, ease and flexibility of ferry travel. The couple set sail with Brittany Ferries from the UK to Spain on a new adventure. They are remote working from Spain and Italy on and off for the rest of the year. Good food, great views and comfortable cabin make for a relaxing journey.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 27 Jun 2023 10:33:56 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jun/27/next-stop-spain-how-to-start-your-european-road-trip-on-the-sea" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jun/15/instaglamour-nerdy-planner-or-freewheeler-take-this-quiz-to-find-out-your-traveller-personality" target="_blank">Instaglamour, nerdy planner or freewheeler? Take this quiz to find out your traveller personality - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Take this quiz to discover what kind of traveller you really are. Some of us just can’t get enough of the likes and follows, while others can't wait to switch off and be at one with a destination. To find out more about hassle-free holidays with Brittany Ferries click here.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 15 Jun 2023 08:41:50 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jun/15/instaglamour-nerdy-planner-or-freewheeler-take-this-quiz-to-find-out-your-traveller-personality" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jul/04/wine-dine-and-relax-why-taking-the-ferry-is-the-ultimate-in-slow-travel" target="_blank">Wine, dine and relax: why taking the ferry is the ultimate in slow travel - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Take a ferry for your European getaway to avoid airport hassles. Enjoy great food on the way and arrive at your destination feeling fresh and ready to go. From the historic chateaux of the Loire valley to the sunshine glamour of the French Riviera, a holiday to France never fails to delight.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 04 Jul 2023 09:30:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jul/04/wine-dine-and-relax-why-taking-the-ferry-is-the-ultimate-in-slow-travel" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jun/15/driving-your-own-car-to-europe-dont-forget-to-take-these-10-essentials-with-you" target="_blank">Driving your own car to Europe? Don’t forget to take these 10 essentials with you - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Brittany Ferries are a great way to start your European holiday with a car. Here are 10 road trip essentials to check before you set off well prepared. Take your car on a Brittany ferries trip to Europe with award-winning service and plenty of space to relax.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 15 Jun 2023 08:42:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jun/15/driving-your-own-car-to-europe-dont-forget-to-take-these-10-essentials-with-you" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/05/how-i-made-friends-with-my-scammer" target="_blank">‘I didn’t trust him. But I was curious about him’: how I made friends with my scammer - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Comedian Michelle Brasier contacted the seller of an online purchase that never turned up. She had no idea it would be the start of an unlikely and troubling friendship. The Australian comedian spent a lot of time in her bathtub - a large clear storage tub in the bottom of her shower – eating bread and watching Buffy the Vampire Slayer.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 09:00:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/05/how-i-made-friends-with-my-scammer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/05/roast-chicken-tomato-green-bean-salad-recipes-yotam-ottolenghi-alfresco-feast" target="_blank">Roast chicken and super salads: Yotam Ottolenghi’s recipes for an alfresco feast - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The secret to alfresco success is prep, so try this trio of make-ahead recipes for size. The apricot-basted chicken with preserved lemon, plus sides of tomato and chickpea, and green beans and aïoli is a hit.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 07:00:35 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/05/roast-chicken-tomato-green-bean-salad-recipes-yotam-ottolenghi-alfresco-feast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/05/arts-and-crafts-schoolhouse-renovation-in-kent-proves-a-class-act" target="_blank">An Arts and Crafts schoolhouse renovation in Kent proves a class act - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Bill and Hayley Kingston bought their atmospheric house in Kent in 2017. Originally an Arts and Crafts schoolhouse built in 1902, it was in a poor state of repair. Divided into two residential properties during the 1970s, its interior bore little resemblance to any original layout.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 15:00:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/05/arts-and-crafts-schoolhouse-renovation-in-kent-proves-a-class-act" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/05/my-lake-district-adventure-a-climb-a-walk-and-a-swim" target="_blank">My Lake District adventure: a climb, a walk and a swim - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Kevin Rushby takes a guided walk across treacherous Morecambe Bay, scales a famous rock needle in Cumbria and dives into Wastwater. To kick off his summer series on UK active breaks, he visits the Wasdale Head Inn in the north of the country.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 13:00:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/05/my-lake-district-adventure-a-climb-a-walk-and-a-swim" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/05/blind-date-sophie-alex" target="_blank">Blind date: ‘Maybe he thought I was very American’ - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Sophie, 26, a product manager, meets Alex, who works in property finance. Sophie hopes to step out of her comfort zone, meet someone new and have a good meal. Alex is a 26-year-old property finance worker and Sophie works in a product management role.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 05:00:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/05/blind-date-sophie-alex" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/05/blondies-cookies-and-smores-cupcake-jemmas-easy-sweet-summer-treats-recipes" target="_blank">Blondies, cookies and s’mores: Cupcake Jemma’s easy sweet summer treats – recipes - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> In summer, for me, it’s all about blondies: Strawberry shortcake blondies. They still have the fudgy texture of a brownie and are hugely versatile. At Crumbs & Doilies, we are always developing new blondie flavours.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 13:00:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/05/blondies-cookies-and-smores-cupcake-jemmas-easy-sweet-summer-treats-recipes" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/aug/01/bride-wades-through-floodwaters-after-philippines-hit-by-typhoons-video-report" target="_blank">Bride wades through floodwaters after Philippines hit by typhoons – video report - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The Philippines was hit with torrential rain over seven days, brought by Typhoon Doksuri and intensified by Typhoon Khanun. Low-lying villages to the north of the country were the worst affected. Residents were forced to travel by small wooden boats and roads were inundated.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 01 Aug 2023 12:10:54 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/aug/01/bride-wades-through-floodwaters-after-philippines-hit-by-typhoons-video-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/31/wildfires-cross-us-border-into-canada-triggering-evacuation-order-video" target="_blank">Wildfires cross US border into Canada triggering evacuation order – video - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Canadian town of Osoyoos ordered to evacuate after wildfire crosses border from Washington state. Firefighters are using water cannon from planes to try to control the blaze, which is estimated to be 885 hectares (2,200 acres) in size. Local authorities estimate the blaze is 885-heater-size.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 31 Jul 2023 08:44:36 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/31/wildfires-cross-us-border-into-canada-triggering-evacuation-order-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">How I survived a 'sex-ed shitstorm' – video - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Cartoonist Fiona Katauskas's book, The Amazing True Story of How Babies are Made, had been on Kmart and Big W shelves for three years. What started as a debate over the offending picture on Facebook would explode over several days into multiple headlines. Here is her take on what happened.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 15:00:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/video/2023/jul/26/sinead-oconnor-the-turbulent-career-of-the-irish-sensation-video-obituary" target="_blank">The life and career of Sinéad O’Connor: ‘I was really a protest singer’ - video obituary - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Sinéad O'Connor has died at the age of 56, prompting grief and tributes. Irish singer abjured conventional stardom for most of her career. Some never forgave her for ripping up a picture of the pope on American TV. The Dubliner enjoyed something of a renaissance in recent years.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 26 Jul 2023 22:06:16 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/video/2023/jul/26/sinead-oconnor-the-turbulent-career-of-the-irish-sensation-video-obituary" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/27/drone-footage-shows-aftermath-of-wildfires-on-2500-year-old-sicilian-temple-video" target="_blank">Drone footage shows aftermath of wildfires on 2,500-year-old Sicilian temple – video - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The temple of Segesta has been turned to ash after days of fires spreading across Sicily. The island has been devastated by wildfires that have killed at least three people. Heatwaves and severe storms have also affected the north of Italy, while heatwaves and storms hit the north.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 15:44:56 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/27/drone-footage-shows-aftermath-of-wildfires-on-2500-year-old-sicilian-temple-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">I was a terrorist. Now I run a kindergarten – video - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Hendi Suhartono was part of a plot to detonate four book bombs and blow up a church in Indonesia. He spent seven years in prison after going through a deradicalisation process. After being released from prison, he received support to open a kindergarten.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 25 Jul 2023 09:15:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/24/greece-wildfires-break-out-corfu-thousands-flee-rhodes-blazes-video-report" target="_blank">Greece: wildfires rage on three islands and mainland – video report - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Firefighters struggling to contain 82 wildfires across the country, 64 of which started on Sunday, the hottest day of the summer so far. As well as huge blazes on Rhodes, 19,000 people were forced to flee the island of Rhodes. Wildfires also broke out on Corfu, Corfu and in the northern Peloponnese region.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 13:09:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/24/greece-wildfires-break-out-corfu-thousands-flee-rhodes-blazes-video-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/24/spain-faces-political-gridlock-after-national-elections-video-report" target="_blank">Spain faces political gridlock after national elections – video report - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Spain appears to be heading for political gridlock after rightwing parties fail to clinch a decisive victory. Pro-independence Catalan and Basque parties as potential kingmakers. Conservative People's party will be given first attempt at trying to cobble together enough votes to win a prime-ministerial investiture vote.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 12:11:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/24/spain-faces-political-gridlock-after-national-elections-video-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">What is supercharging the global heat? – video explainer - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The planet is being hit with a double whammy of global heating in 2023: on top of the rise in global temperature caused by greenhouse gas emissions is an emerging El Niño. This sporadic event is the biggest natural influence on year-to-year weather and adds a further spurt of warmth to an already overheating world.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 16:48:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Kids v cars: the campaign to reclaim children's play space on British streets – video - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Playing Out is helping to close streets to cars to reclaim the space on children’s doorsteps. Some experts say a growing mental and physical health crisis could be a result. Families are campaigning for children to have fun outdoors again. The Guardian's Harriet Grant travels to Bristol to meet Playing Out.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 11 Jul 2023 09:30:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Inside the NHS as staff say future hangs in the balance – video - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The NHS was launched in 1948 by Labour MP Aneurin Bevan, inspired in part by the Tredegar Medical Aid Society in his constituency. It has since saved millions of lives and inspired health systems around the world. Seventy-five years on, the Guardian video team was given access to NHS services in south Wales town.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 04 Jul 2023 10:19:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jun/22/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-extreme-heatwave-hitting-our-oceans-video-explainer" target="_blank">What you need to know about the 'extreme' heatwave hitting our oceans – video explainer - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Sea temperatures, particularly off the north-east coast of England and west of Ireland, are several degrees above normal, breaking records for late spring and early summer. The Met Office has said that according to records dating to 1850, global sea surface temperatures in April and May reached an all-time high.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 22 Jun 2023 14:22:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jun/22/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-extreme-heatwave-hitting-our-oceans-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jul/24/tell-us-how-have-you-been-affected-by-wildfires-on-corfu" target="_blank">Greeks: tell us about the aftermath of the wildfires - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> We’d like to hear from local people about the impact of wildfires in regions including Rhodes, Magnesia, Corfu and Evia. Have you been affected? Have you had to evacuate? Has your home or business been damaged? We want to speak with local people on the situation where they are.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 10:03:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jul/24/tell-us-how-have-you-been-affected-by-wildfires-on-corfu" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/03/uk-workers-over-50-share-your-experience-of-being-a-food-courier" target="_blank">UK workers over 50: share your experience of being a food courier - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Work and pensions secretary, Mel Stride, made the comments during a visit to Deliveroo HQ. Deliveroo has recorded a 62% increase in riders aged over 50 since 2021. We're interested to hear from people aged 50 and over in the UK about what it’s like to work as couriers.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 11:29:13 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/03/uk-workers-over-50-share-your-experience-of-being-a-food-courier" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/03/uk-film-and-tv-workers-how-are-hollywood-strikes-affecting-you" target="_blank">UK film and TV workers: how are Hollywood strikes affecting you? - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> US actors’ union Sag-Aftra joined the Writers Guild of America (WGA) on strike over contract negotiations. Hollywood actors and writers have been on strike at the same time for over six decades. We want to hear how strikes are impacting the UK film and TV industry.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 16:12:39 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/03/uk-film-and-tv-workers-how-are-hollywood-strikes-affecting-you" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jul/26/people-in-turkey-and-syria-what-has-life-been-like-since-the-february-earthquakes" target="_blank">People in Turkey and Syria: what has life been like since the February earthquakes? - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> We’d like to hear from people who were affected by the two devastating earthquakes of 7.8 and 7.6 magnitude on 6 February in Turkey and Syria. We want to know what their lives have been like since the disaster, and how their family and community have been affected.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 26 Jul 2023 11:52:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jul/26/people-in-turkey-and-syria-what-has-life-been-like-since-the-february-earthquakes" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/04/donald-trump-january-6-indictment-podcast" target="_blank">Donald Trump’s January 6 indictment - podcast - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The former US president appeared in court on Wednesday charged on four counts related to his efforts to overturn the result of the 2020 election. The former president faces four counts: conspiracy to defraud the United States; conspiracy to obstruct an official proceeding; obstruction of and attempt to obstruct a proceeding; and conspiracy against rights.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 02:00:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/04/donald-trump-january-6-indictment-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/audio/2023/aug/05/weekend-podcast-at-home-with-world-heavyweight-champion-tyson-fury-john-crace-on-rishis-climate-retreat-and-comedian-michelle-brasier-on-befriending-her-scammer" target="_blank">Weekend podcast: at home with world heavyweight champion Tyson Fury, John Crace on Rishi’s climate retreat, and comedian Michelle Brasier on befriending her scammer - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Tyson Fury weighs in on marriage, mental health and life as a multimillionaire in Morecambe. John Crace looks on as the PM gaslights the UK with his North Sea plan while the world burns. Michelle Brasier explains why she befriended her scammer.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 04:00:31 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/audio/2023/aug/05/weekend-podcast-at-home-with-world-heavyweight-champion-tyson-fury-john-crace-on-rishis-climate-retreat-and-comedian-michelle-brasier-on-befriending-her-scammer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/audio/2023/aug/04/al-sharpton-on-60-years-since-the-civil-rights-march-on-washington-podcast" target="_blank">Al Sharpton on 60 years since the civil rights march on Washington – podcast - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> On 26 August, Rev Al Sharpton, Martin Luther King III, and other civil rights activists will commemorate the 1963 march on Washington. Jonathan Freedland sits down with Sharpton to discuss why he believes King's 'I have a dream' speech has been abused by some on the right. He also discusses why he is still fighting for police reform.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 04:00:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/audio/2023/aug/04/al-sharpton-on-60-years-since-the-civil-rights-march-on-washington-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/04/best-of-2023-so-far-battle-of-the-botanic-garden-the-horticulture-war-roiling-the-isle-of-wight-podcast" target="_blank">Best of 2023 … so far: Battle of the botanic garden: the horticulture war roiling the Isle of Wight – podcast - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Every Friday in August we will publish some of our favourite audio long reads of 2023. This week, from February, features a US businessman taking over a beloved garden. He decided on a radical new approach, all in the name of sustainability. But angry critics claim it’s just plain neglect.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 04:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/04/best-of-2023-so-far-battle-of-the-botanic-garden-the-horticulture-war-roiling-the-isle-of-wight-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/03/underdogs-bite-back-as-germany-and-brazil-crash-out-womens-football-weekly" target="_blank">Underdogs bite back as Germany and Brazil crash out – Women’s Football Weekly - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Faye Carruthers is joined by Jo Khan, Chris Paouros and Claire Rafferty to wrap up an explosive final set of group games. The two-time world champions Germany are out of the World Cup, while Morocco make more history - the second lowest ranked team in the tournament are into the last 16.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 17:33:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/03/underdogs-bite-back-as-germany-and-brazil-crash-out-womens-football-weekly" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/audio/2023/aug/03/summer-picks-could-the-multiverse-be-real-podcast" target="_blank">Summer picks: could the multiverse be real? | podcast - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The film Everything Everywhere All at Once won the 2023 Academy Award for Best Picture. Ian Sample spoke to theoretical physicist and philosopher Sean Carroll about why we seem to be drawn to the idea of multiple worlds, and what the science says about how the multiverse might actually work.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 04:00:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category">