guardian.com/world/2023/aug/04/fighting-two-enemies-ukraine-female-soldiers-decry-harassment" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/05/waterparks-bring-palestinians-summer-relief-from-bleak-reality-of-israeli-occupation" target="_blank">Waterparks bring Palestinians summer relief from bleak reality of Israeli occupation - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> West Bank city of Jericho, north of the Dead Sea, is the lowest-elevation city in the world. Temperatures in the oasis town in the Jordan Valley can exceed 40C (104F) in the summer months, making water a more precious resource than ever. Despite strict limits on its water supply, the city has seen a surge in aqua parks.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 14:02:36 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/05/waterparks-bring-palestinians-summer-relief-from-bleak-reality-of-israeli-occupation" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/aug/05/skeletal-editing-chemistry-molecule-atom-medicine-drug-development-sustainable" target="_blank">‘Endless possibilities’: the chemists changing molecules atom by atom - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> A new method called ‘skeletal editing’ offers a hugely simplified way to alter matter, paving the way for world-changing innovations in personalised medicine and sustainable plastics. ‘We’re one of the only fields of science that at its core is about making things that have never existed anywhere else in the universe,” says associate professor of chemistry at the University of Chicago.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 13:00:42 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/aug/05/skeletal-editing-chemistry-molecule-atom-medicine-drug-development-sustainable" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/05/trump-fake-electors-georgia" target="_blank">Inside Trump’s ‘alternate electors’ plot to steal the vote in Georgia - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Greg Bluestein was one of a handful of reporters who were to witness the casting of electoral college votes which would officially hand Joe Biden victory in the critical battleground state – and with it the US presidency. We piece together the astonishing story of how 16 men and women tried to reshape the course of US history.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 12:00:41 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/05/trump-fake-electors-georgia" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/05/louisiana-catholic-priest-abuse-reform-church" target="_blank">‘Evil does exist’: Louisiana victim of Catholic priest abuse urges reform - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Tim Gioe, 36, is pressing for parental consent to be obtained before priests are left alone with children. Patrick Wattigny groomed him for sexual abuse, of which the clergyman was recently convicted. Gioi and his wife, Sarah, who are raising three sons together, are advocating for schools and other parochial institutions to obtain fully informed parental consent.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 12:00:41 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/05/louisiana-catholic-priest-abuse-reform-church" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/04/electric-cars-culture-wars-evs" target="_blank">How electric cars became a battleground in the culture wars - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Tesla driver was caught by a ‘rolling coal’, a deliberate modification of a diesel engine to increase the engine’s horsepower. Sinister Diesel, one of the companies selling ‘defeat devices’ used to roll coal, agreed to pay a $1m (£780,000) fine this week for breaking environmental laws.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 13:00:14 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/04/electric-cars-culture-wars-evs" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2022/sep/20/sign-up-for-the-fashion-statement-newsletter-our-free-fashion-email" target="_blank">Sign up for the Fashion Statement newsletter: our free fashion email - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Style, with substance: what’s really trending this week, a roundup of the best fashion journalism and your wardrobe dilemmas solved, delivered straight to your inbox every Thursday. Find out what's really trending and what you need to look at this week's top fashion stories.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 20 Sep 2022 11:06:20 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></